36bool HasOnlyStringMaps(JSHeapBroker* broker, ZoneVector<MapRef> const& maps) {
37 for (MapRef map : maps) {
38 if (!map.IsStringMap()) return false;
39 }
40 return true;
41}

43namespace {

45bool HasOnlyNumberMaps(JSHeapBroker* broker, ZoneVector<MapRef> const& maps) {
46 for (MapRef map : maps) {
47 if (map.instance_type() != HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE) return false;
48 }
49 return true;
50}

54bool PropertyAccessBuilder::TryBuildStringCheck(JSHeapBroker* broker,
55 ZoneVector<MapRef> const& maps,
56 Node** receiver, Effect* effect,
57 Control control) {
58 if (HasOnlyStringMaps(broker, maps)) {
59 // Monormorphic string access (ignoring the fact that there are multiple
60 // String maps).
61 *receiver = *effect =
62 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(FeedbackSource()), *receiver,
63 *effect, control);
64 return true;
65 }
66 return false;
67}
68
69bool PropertyAccessBuilder::TryBuildNumberCheck(JSHeapBroker* broker,
70 ZoneVector<MapRef> const& maps,
71 Node** receiver, Effect* effect,
72 Control control) {
73 if (HasOnlyNumberMaps(broker, maps)) {
74 // Monomorphic number access (we also deal with Smis here).
75 *receiver = *effect =
76 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckNumber(FeedbackSource()), *receiver,
77 *effect, control);
78 return true;
79 }
80 return false;
81}

83void PropertyAccessBuilder::BuildCheckMaps(Node* object, Effect* effect,
84 Control control,
85 ZoneVector<MapRef> const& maps) {
86 HeapObjectMatcher m(object);
87 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
88 MapRef object_map = m.Ref(broker()).map(broker());
89 if (object_map.is_stable()) {
90 for (MapRef map : maps) {
91 if (map.equals(object_map)) {
92 dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(object_map);
93 return;
94 }
95 }
96 }
97 }
98 ZoneRefSet<Map> map_set;
99 CheckMapsFlags flags = CheckMapsFlag::kNone;
100 for (MapRef map : maps) {
101 map_set.insert(map, graph()->zone());
102 if (map.is_migration_target()) {
103 flags |= CheckMapsFlag::kTryMigrateInstance;
104 }
105 }
106 *effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckMaps(flags, map_set), object,
107 *effect, control);
108}
109
110Node* PropertyAccessBuilder::BuildCheckValue(Node* receiver, Effect* effect,
111 Control control,
112 Handle<HeapObject> value) {
113 HeapObjectMatcher m(receiver);
114 if (m.Is(value)) return receiver;
115 Node* expected = jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(value);
116 Node* check =
117 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), receiver, expected);
118 *effect =
119 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue),
120 check, *effect, control);
121 return expected;
122}

124Node* PropertyAccessBuilder::ResolveHolder(
125 PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info, Node* lookup_start_object) {
126 OptionalJSObjectRef holder = access_info.holder();
127 if (holder.has_value()) {
128 return jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(holder.value(), broker());
129 }
130 return lookup_start_object;
131}
132
133MachineRepresentation PropertyAccessBuilder::ConvertRepresentation(
134 Representation representation) {
135 switch (representation.kind()) {
136 case Representation::kSmi:
137 return MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned;
138 case Representation::kDouble:
139 return MachineRepresentation::kFloat64;
140 case Representation::kHeapObject:
141 return MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer;
142 case Representation::kTagged:
143 return MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
144 default:
145 UNREACHABLE();
146 }
147}

149base::Optional<Node*> PropertyAccessBuilder::FoldLoadDictPrototypeConstant(
150 PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info) {
151 DCHECK(V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL);
152 DCHECK(access_info.IsDictionaryProtoDataConstant());
153
154 InternalIndex index = access_info.dictionary_index();
155 OptionalObjectRef value = access_info.holder()->GetOwnDictionaryProperty(
156 broker(), index, dependencies());
157 if (!value) return {};
158
159 for (MapRef map : access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()) {
160 Handle<Map> map_handle = map.object();
161 // Non-JSReceivers that passed AccessInfoFactory::ComputePropertyAccessInfo
162 // must have different lookup start map.
163 if (!IsJSReceiverMap(*map_handle)) {
164 // Perform the implicit ToObject for primitives here.
165 // Implemented according to ES6 section 7.3.2 GetV (V, P).
166 Tagged<JSFunction> constructor =
167 Map::GetConstructorFunction(
168 *map_handle, *broker()->target_native_context().object())
169 .value();
170 // {constructor.initial_map()} is loaded/stored with acquire-release
171 // semantics for constructors.
172 map = MakeRefAssumeMemoryFence(broker(), constructor->initial_map());
173 DCHECK(IsJSObjectMap(*map.object()));
174 }
175 dependencies()->DependOnConstantInDictionaryPrototypeChain(
176 map, access_info.name(), value.value(), PropertyKind::kData);
177 }
178
179 return jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(value.value(), broker());
180}

182Node* PropertyAccessBuilder::TryFoldLoadConstantDataField(
183 NameRef name, PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info,
184 Node* lookup_start_object) {
185 if (!access_info.IsFastDataConstant()) return nullptr;
186
187 // First, determine if we have a constant holder to load from.
188 OptionalJSObjectRef holder = access_info.holder();
189
190 // If {access_info} has a holder, just use it.
191 if (!holder.has_value()) {
192 // Otherwise, try to match the {lookup_start_object} as a constant.
193 HeapObjectMatcher m(lookup_start_object);
194 if (!m.HasResolvedValue() || !m.Ref(broker()).IsJSObject()) return nullptr;
195
196 // Let us make sure the actual map of the constant lookup_start_object is
197 // among the maps in {access_info}.
198 MapRef lookup_start_object_map = m.Ref(broker()).map(broker());
199 if (std::find_if(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().begin(),
200 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().end(),
201 [&](MapRef map) {
202 return map.equals(lookup_start_object_map);
203 }) == access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().end()) {
204 // The map of the lookup_start_object is not in the feedback, let us bail
205 // out.
206 return nullptr;
207 }
208 holder = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSObject();
209 }
210
211 if (access_info.field_representation().IsDouble()) {
212 base::Optional<Float64> value = holder->GetOwnFastConstantDoubleProperty(
213 broker(), access_info.field_index(), dependencies());
214 return value.has_value() ? jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(value->get_scalar())
215 : nullptr;
216 }
217 OptionalObjectRef value = holder->GetOwnFastConstantDataProperty(
218 broker(), access_info.field_representation(), access_info.field_index(),
219 dependencies());
220 return value.has_value() ? jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*value, broker())
221 : nullptr;
222}

224Node* PropertyAccessBuilder::BuildLoadDataField(NameRef name, Node* holder,
225 FieldAccess&& field_access,
226 bool is_inobject, Node** effect,
227 Node** control) {
228 Node* storage = holder;
229 if (!is_inobject) {
230 storage = *effect = graph()->NewNode(
231 simplified()->LoadField(
232 AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer()),
233 storage, *effect, *control);
234 }
235 if (field_access.machine_type.representation() ==
236 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
237 if (dependencies() == nullptr) {
238 FieldAccess const storage_access = {kTaggedBase,
239 field_access.offset,
240 name.object(),
241 OptionalMapRef(),
242 Type::Any(),
243 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
244 kPointerWriteBarrier,
245 "BuildLoadDataField",
246 field_access.const_field_info};
247 storage = *effect = graph()->NewNode(
248 simplified()->LoadField(storage_access), storage, *effect, *control);
249 // We expect the loaded value to be a heap number here. With
250 // in-place field representation changes it is possible this is a
251 // no longer a heap number without map transitions. If we haven't taken
252 // a dependency on field representation, we should verify the loaded
253 // value is a heap number.
254 storage = *effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckHeapObject(),
255 storage, *effect, *control);
256 Node* map = *effect =
257 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
258 storage, *effect, *control);
259 Node* is_heap_number =
260 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), map,
261 jsgraph()->HeapNumberMapConstant());
262 *effect = graph()->NewNode(
263 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber),
264 is_heap_number, *effect, *control);
265 } else {
266 FieldAccess const storage_access = {kTaggedBase,
267 field_access.offset,
268 name.object(),
269 OptionalMapRef(),
270 Type::OtherInternal(),
271 MachineType::TaggedPointer(),
272 kPointerWriteBarrier,
273 "BuildLoadDataField",
274 field_access.const_field_info};
275 storage = *effect = graph()->NewNode(
276 simplified()->LoadField(storage_access), storage, *effect, *control);
277 }
278 FieldAccess value_field_access = AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue();
279 value_field_access.const_field_info = field_access.const_field_info;
280 field_access = value_field_access;
281 }
282 Node* value = *effect = graph()->NewNode(
283 simplified()->LoadField(field_access), storage, *effect, *control);
284 return value;
285}
286
287Node* PropertyAccessBuilder::BuildLoadDataField(
288 NameRef name, PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info,
289 Node* lookup_start_object, Node** effect, Node** control) {
290 DCHECK(access_info.IsDataField() || access_info.IsFastDataConstant());
291
292 if (Node* value = TryFoldLoadConstantDataField(name, access_info,
293 lookup_start_object)) {
294 return value;
295 }
296
297 MachineRepresentation const field_representation =
298 ConvertRepresentation(access_info.field_representation());
299 Node* storage = ResolveHolder(access_info, lookup_start_object);
300
301 FieldAccess field_access = {
302 kTaggedBase,
303 access_info.field_index().offset(),
304 name.object(),
305 OptionalMapRef(),
306 access_info.field_type(),
307 MachineType::TypeForRepresentation(field_representation),
308 kFullWriteBarrier,
309 "BuildLoadDataField",
310 access_info.GetConstFieldInfo()};
311 if (field_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer ||
312 field_representation == MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer) {
313 // Remember the map of the field value, if its map is stable. This is
314 // used by the LoadElimination to eliminate map checks on the result.
315 OptionalMapRef field_map = access_info.field_map();
316 if (field_map.has_value()) {
317 if (field_map->is_stable()) {
318 dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(field_map.value());
319 field_access.map = field_map;
320 }
321 }
322 }
323 return BuildLoadDataField(name, storage, std::move(field_access),
324 access_info.field_index().is_inobject(), effect,
325 control);
326}
